  sodium: 1460 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Remove any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; roughly chop leaves. Dice @Roma tomato{2}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Halve @pre-cooked turkey meatballs{8%ounce}.

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} in a large, wide #pot over medium-high heat.

> TIP: Use a pot or pan as wide as the spaghetti is long—ideally 11 inches or wider.

Add meatballs and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate.

Return same #pot to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon}. Add kale and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Transfer to #plate with meatballs.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in same #pot over medium-high heat. Add @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}(half for 4 servings); cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in tomatoes, @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @water{2%cups}, and @salt{1/2%tsp}.

> TIP: Cut top off carton of cream sauce to open fully; transfer contents, using a spoon or spatula to scrape sauce from carton sides.

Add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot with sauce; lay noodles as flat as possible (they should be mostly submerged in liquid).

> TIP: Break noodles in half if your pot isn't wide enough for them to lay flat.

Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium low.

Simmer, stirring occasionally and making sure noodles stay submerged, ~{15%minutes}. (At this point, spaghetti should be malleable but not yet fully cooked; sauce will be slightly thickened.)

Once spaghetti has cooked 15 minutes, return meatballs and kale to #pot. Cook, stirring, until spaghetti is al dente and sauce has thickened and coats noodles, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

> TIP: If sauce thickens too much before pasta is tender, add splashes of water as needed.

Remove #pot from heat.

Taste and season pasta with salt and pepper. Stir in lemon zest and a big squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and top with @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.